  "prompt": "What is the difference between on and off premise catering?",
  "response": "On-premise and off-premise catering differ in the location where the food is prepared and served:\n\nOn-Premise Catering:\n- Food is prepared and served at the same location\n- Typically occurs at venues with their own kitchen facilities\n- Examples include restaurants, hotels, banquet halls, and event spaces\n- Easier to maintain food quality and temperature\n- Usually has more elaborate presentation options\n- Often more convenient for guests\n\nOff-Premise Catering:\n- Food is prepared at a separate location and transported to the event site\n- Can be served at various venues like outdoor spaces, homes, parks, or other locations without kitchen facilities\n- Requires more logistical planning for food transportation and temperature control\n- May have more limited menu options due to transportation constraints\n- Typically more flexible in terms of venue selection\n- Often used for weddings, corporate events, parties, and other special occasions\n\nThe main differences are in food preparation, logistics, and venue flexibility between these two catering styles.",
